    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLES: SPICER J400-S, W460-S - DISASSEMBLE - INTERMEDIATE CASE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="6">
        <title>INTERMEDIATE CASE</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift clutch shift collar and shift fork from case. Inspect shift fork for wear and
                misalignment (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400430">Figure 30</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400430" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400430" filename="../figg14/G1400430.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 30. Lift Clutch Shift Collar and Shift Fork From Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove input gear assembly from intermediate case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400431">Figure 31</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400431" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400431" filename="../figg14/G1400431.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 31. Remove Input Gear Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bearing from input gear using a suitable puller (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400432">Figure 32</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400432" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400432" filename="../figg14/G1400432.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Remove Bearing From Input Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Turn gear over and remove opposite bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400433">Figure 33</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400433" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400433" filename="../figg14/G1400433.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Remove Opposite Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place intermediate case in soft jawed vise clamping on the flats of the idler shaft. Remove
                idler shaft nut using a torque multiplier wrench (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400434">Figure 34</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400434" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400434" filename="../figg14/G1400434.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 34. Remove Idler Shaft Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove intermediate case from vise. Tap idler shaft with a soft hammer to free from case and
                remove idler shaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide idler gear to large opening and remove idler gear, bearings and bearing spacer. Be
                sure to retain bearing spacer for possible use during reassembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400435">Figure 35</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400435" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400435" filename="../figg14/G1400435.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 35. Remove Idler Gear, Bearings and Bearing Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
